 Port Elizabeth - Bethelsdorp police on Friday appealed to the public for assistance with information  that can help them trace a missing 62-year-old woman. Menkiwe Dyakala was last seen walking in Rensburg Street on Thursday afternoon. According to police information, Dyakala was walking with a family member when she got agitated and angry and walked away from the person. Police spokesperson, Capt Priscilla Naidu said that "According to family, Dyakala is mentally unstable and usually display such behaviour when she does not take her medication. "She resides in Slovo Street in Govan Mbeki in Kwadwesi." When she did not return home later that afternoon, her family reported her missing at about 20:00. "She is in urgent need of medication," Col Naidu said. "Anyone who can assist in tracing Dyakala or may know of her whereabouts is asked to contact D/W/O Ben Killian at SAPS Bethesldorp on 072 342 7434 o their nearest police station." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 